CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 29, 1952, pg. 11, reads: "Bride - Mary Jane Harris, daughter of Mrs. Maude Harris, became the bride of Hubert Moton March in a charming home ceremony. Given away by her brother, the bride was a lovely picture as she repeated her vows.  Attendants were Helen Steward and Lornell Davis. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of bride Mary Jane Harris Moton wearing sheer fingerless gloves, seated on arm of sofa, in home
